\begin{align*}3 \star 5 &= \left( (3+5)5 \right) \\ &= \left( 85 \right) \\ &= 40\end{align*}

\begin{align*}5 \star 3 &= \left( (5+3)3 \right) \\ &= \left( 83 \right) \\ &= 24\end{align*}

Next, we subtract the second result from the first.
\begin{align*}(3 \star 5) - (5 \star 3) &= 40 - 24 \\ &= 16\end{align*}

So $ (3\star5) - (5\star3) = \boxed{16} $.</think> <answer>16</answer>

